WEBVTT

00:01:34.523 --> 00:01:37.444
A truly pathetic hole
in the wall you have here.

00:01:39.323 --> 00:01:40.827
-[ASHIYA] Sire.
-Thank you.

00:01:44.876 --> 00:01:45.837
[ASHIYA]
Lovely.

00:01:46.713 --> 00:01:49.051
A gift from the Malebranche.

00:01:49.135 --> 00:01:50.470
Freebies are far less thrilling

00:01:50.555 --> 00:01:51.932
when they're coming
from traitors.

00:01:52.015 --> 00:01:53.853
You couldn't pay me
to touch that thing.

00:01:54.353 --> 00:01:55.397
Oh, good.

00:01:55.815 --> 00:01:58.486
So I guess you guys aren't going
to go along with those meanies?

00:01:58.571 --> 00:01:59.405
Of course not.

00:01:59.948 --> 00:02:00.825
[chuckles]

00:02:01.743 --> 00:02:02.954
Hey, Chiho.

00:02:03.037 --> 00:02:04.081
How did you manage to cross

00:02:04.165 --> 00:02:05.626
right through
Erone's force field?

00:02:05.710 --> 00:02:07.589
That magic was, like,
industrial grade.

00:02:07.672 --> 00:02:11.847
Well, my speculation is that
it had to do with Chiho's ring.

00:02:11.930 --> 00:02:14.811
I believe it shares
a sephiric origin with Erone.

00:02:16.189 --> 00:02:17.107
-[sips]
-[gasps]

00:02:17.191 --> 00:02:18.276
Our issue...

00:02:18.694 --> 00:02:21.867
Is that corporate-costumed fool,
his demonic master.

00:02:21.950 --> 00:02:22.911
Yes, I agree.

00:02:23.829 --> 00:02:25.040
Wait, one moment!

00:02:25.666 --> 00:02:28.004
You know of Alas Ramus
and the other sephirah?

00:02:28.087 --> 00:02:29.423
Yes, of course.

00:02:29.508 --> 00:02:30.383
That being said,

00:02:30.467 --> 00:02:33.891
Geburah's recent recruitment was
completely unbeknownst to me.

00:02:33.974 --> 00:02:35.268
[sips and screams]

00:02:35.352 --> 00:02:36.939
Who poured this abomination?

00:02:37.022 --> 00:02:38.609
Hot tea
is entirely inappropriate

00:02:38.692 --> 00:02:40.530
-in this weather!
-[chuckles]

00:02:40.613 --> 00:02:41.657
What's the prob?

00:02:41.740 --> 00:02:43.786
If he's just doing
what Farfarello says,

00:02:43.869 --> 00:02:45.121
let's forget the kid for now

00:02:45.205 --> 00:02:47.042
and kick that demon's
sharply-dressed ass.

00:02:47.125 --> 00:02:49.296
-You're a fool.
-[gasps]

00:02:49.380 --> 00:02:51.217
If we defeat Farfarello now,

00:02:51.300 --> 00:02:53.889
they'll send a stronger opponent
in his stead.

00:02:53.973 --> 00:02:56.562
Ideally, we convince him
to leave on his own.

00:02:56.645 --> 00:02:58.189
If we play
into his sense of reason

00:02:58.273 --> 00:03:00.528
and speak rationally with him,
we have a chance.

00:03:00.611 --> 00:03:03.576
Well, we're on the wrong foot.

00:03:03.659 --> 00:03:05.788
And that's not the only way
I fudged up.

00:03:05.872 --> 00:03:07.291
♪

00:03:07.374 --> 00:03:09.754
I instinctively protected Chi
from him.

00:03:09.838 --> 00:03:11.800
And unless
he's a complete idiot,

00:03:11.884 --> 00:03:14.514
he could tell that she's someone
we know and care about.

00:03:14.598 --> 00:03:15.808
And...

00:03:15.892 --> 00:03:18.229
And he probably saw
I couldn't protect myself,

00:03:18.313 --> 00:03:19.524
that I can't fight.

00:03:19.608 --> 00:03:20.943
What does that mean?

00:03:21.027 --> 00:03:22.362
[blows]

00:03:22.446 --> 00:03:25.201
Well, I know what I would do.
Kidnap you.

00:03:25.285 --> 00:03:26.454
[all gasp]

00:03:26.538 --> 00:03:28.207
Don't look so shocked.

00:03:28.291 --> 00:03:31.172
If it wasn't a good plan,
I wouldn't have done it myself.

00:03:32.007 --> 00:03:33.802
It's exactly as I feared.

00:03:36.015 --> 00:03:38.102
I need you, Mister Sariel.

00:03:38.186 --> 00:03:40.608
Would you pretty please help me
take my idea linking

00:03:40.691 --> 00:03:41.818
to the next level?

00:03:42.402 --> 00:03:43.404
[all gasp]

00:03:43.488 --> 00:03:44.658
Are you insane?

00:03:44.741 --> 00:03:46.953
Why would I spend my time
doing something for you?

00:03:47.037 --> 00:03:49.208
I understand
it's not a small favor.

00:03:49.291 --> 00:03:50.293
To repay you,

00:03:50.377 --> 00:03:53.091
I'll try and make things right
between you and Miss Kisaki.

00:03:53.174 --> 00:03:54.218
[gasp]

00:03:54.301 --> 00:03:56.723
Now!
Let the training begin, soldier!

00:03:56.807 --> 00:03:57.975
Sir!

00:03:58.059 --> 00:04:00.898
Calling it now. This ends bad.

00:04:00.981 --> 00:04:02.234
We have no choice.

00:04:02.317 --> 00:04:05.490
The shrinking angel's lame,
but not our biggest problem.

00:04:05.574 --> 00:04:08.914
If we win over Farfarello,
there are no problems.

00:04:08.997 --> 00:04:10.793
This all will end peacefully.

00:04:10.876 --> 00:04:11.920
This must work.

00:04:12.003 --> 00:04:14.718
Miss Sasaki is a vital part
of His Majesty's plan,

00:04:14.801 --> 00:04:17.515
thus we need this brute
to take her seriously.

00:04:17.598 --> 00:04:18.433
Yeah.

00:04:19.059 --> 00:04:21.940
A flashy holy spell might make
her look like less of a joke,

00:04:22.023 --> 00:04:23.902
but it still seems risky.

00:04:23.986 --> 00:04:27.492
It's a gamble.
But the only play we've got.

00:04:27.577 --> 00:04:31.417
[CHIHO] ♪ <i>The sun is up
It's morning once again ♪</i>

00:04:31.501 --> 00:04:35.926
<i>♪ The day is full of hope, so ♪</i>

00:04:36.010 --> 00:04:37.053
Interesting.

00:04:37.137 --> 00:04:39.057
If you can get
to a clear state of mind,

00:04:39.141 --> 00:04:40.561
it doesn't matter how.

00:04:41.187 --> 00:04:42.732
[EMI]
I used hymns to train.

00:04:43.441 --> 00:04:45.571
I don't think
I ever told her that, though.

00:04:45.654 --> 00:04:46.698
Sure.

00:04:46.782 --> 00:04:49.328
But, why
this radio calisthenics song?

00:04:49.411 --> 00:04:52.543
Easy! This one always makes me
super happy!

00:04:53.377 --> 00:04:56.425
Bel! Try sending the songbird
something!

00:04:56.510 --> 00:04:58.471
If she can get a handle
on receiving,

00:04:58.555 --> 00:05:00.183
perhaps understanding
the sensation

00:05:00.266 --> 00:05:02.437
will help her send out
a message of her own!

00:05:02.522 --> 00:05:03.732
[SUZUNO]
Prepare thyself!

00:05:03.816 --> 00:05:05.068
Thanks for your help!

00:05:05.528 --> 00:05:08.575
[SUZUNO]
Let's see. What shall I say?

00:05:08.659 --> 00:05:10.411
It should be something
that will trigger her

00:05:10.495 --> 00:05:13.084
to reverse my desired flow
of communication.

00:05:14.461 --> 00:05:15.463
[clears throat]

00:05:15.548 --> 00:05:16.591
Good Chiho.

00:05:17.259 --> 00:05:18.554
You want to ma...

00:05:18.637 --> 00:05:22.102
Or, uh, exchange nuptial vows
with the Devil, do you not?

00:05:22.185 --> 00:05:23.856
[whimpers]

00:05:23.939 --> 00:05:25.483
[scream]

00:05:25.568 --> 00:05:27.487
The hell? Chi?

00:05:27.572 --> 00:05:28.824
[whimpering]

00:05:28.907 --> 00:05:31.036
[yelps] You heard nothing,
you heard nothing!

00:05:31.120 --> 00:05:32.122
[whimpers]

00:05:32.205 --> 00:05:33.124
[gasps]

00:05:33.207 --> 00:05:34.126
-[grunts]
-[whimpers]

00:05:35.420 --> 00:05:36.422
And with that display,

00:05:36.506 --> 00:05:38.844
my pupil has overcome
her first hurdle.

00:05:38.927 --> 00:05:41.140
Judging by the way
Bel received her idea link,

00:05:41.223 --> 00:05:43.729
Chiho fired off
quite a powerful response.

00:05:43.812 --> 00:05:46.943
[groans] I was concerned
that my skull had fractured.

00:05:49.824 --> 00:05:50.659
[SARUE]
Well, everyone.

00:05:50.743 --> 00:05:52.788
Should we plan on training again
tomorrow?

00:05:52.872 --> 00:05:54.709
Same time, same place?

00:05:54.792 --> 00:05:56.462
That suits us fine.

00:05:56.546 --> 00:05:57.882
If I reserve the space now,

00:05:57.965 --> 00:06:00.971
there's a healthy window of time
open between one and four.

00:06:01.055 --> 00:06:02.558
Sir Schedule over here.

00:06:02.642 --> 00:06:04.436
Will that time slot work for--

00:06:04.520 --> 00:06:07.359
-Uh...
-Uh, something up, Sariel?

00:06:09.321 --> 00:06:10.741
Oh, my gosh!

00:06:10.824 --> 00:06:14.039
Huh? Whoa, hey, gang,
fancy meeting you here.

00:06:14.582 --> 00:06:16.711
I wasn't expecting
to see anyone this late.

00:06:17.672 --> 00:06:20.093
Yeah, same here. How weird.

00:06:20.176 --> 00:06:23.600
Well, if it isn't Sarue.
What are you doing here?

00:06:23.684 --> 00:06:26.523
Oh, yes!
Well, you see, I, I was--

00:06:26.606 --> 00:06:28.986
It's a funny story! We, uh--

00:06:29.069 --> 00:06:30.405
[KISAKI]
You fool.

00:06:30.488 --> 00:06:32.743
If you messed with my crew
or my customers,

00:06:32.827 --> 00:06:33.996
you'll live to regret it.

00:06:34.706 --> 00:06:38.379
I just... live here! I swear!
[whimpering]

00:06:38.462 --> 00:06:40.133
Oh. Nice place.

00:06:40.216 --> 00:06:41.260
[gasps]

00:06:41.594 --> 00:06:44.266
That's my dream,
I want to join their ranks.

00:06:44.349 --> 00:06:45.811
Wait, Miss Kisaki.

00:06:45.894 --> 00:06:47.147
Don't tell me
you're quitting Mg--

00:06:47.230 --> 00:06:49.986
No. Don't panic, okay?

00:06:50.069 --> 00:06:53.994
But, uh, I know I've been acting
a little distant

00:06:54.077 --> 00:06:55.371
the past few days.

00:06:55.873 --> 00:06:57.668
I blame the new MgCafé.

00:06:58.169 --> 00:06:59.881
It reawakened something.

00:06:59.964 --> 00:07:02.177
A dream I've kept tucked away
for a while.

00:07:02.260 --> 00:07:04.682
-You, uh, have dreams?
-Huh?

00:07:04.766 --> 00:07:05.684
Of course.

00:07:06.143 --> 00:07:08.147
They're not
just for crazy kiddos like you,

00:07:08.230 --> 00:07:09.191
you know.

00:07:09.274 --> 00:07:11.153
[KISAKI] I want to see
if I could do it.

00:07:11.236 --> 00:07:12.782
If I could keep my head
above water

00:07:12.865 --> 00:07:14.827
without having a big name
to lean on.

00:07:16.413 --> 00:07:18.543
So, does that mean
that you're planning

00:07:18.627 --> 00:07:20.964
to start your very own cafe
down the line?

00:07:21.048 --> 00:07:21.883
Maybe.

00:07:21.966 --> 00:07:23.469
But it's much less
of a solid plan,

00:07:23.553 --> 00:07:25.849
and more
of a "that would be nice."

00:07:26.391 --> 00:07:28.270
But you're looking
for real estate.

00:07:28.354 --> 00:07:31.068
Seems like
a pretty concrete step to me.

00:07:31.151 --> 00:07:33.447
[KISAKI] There's still a lot
that I need MgRonald's for.

00:07:33.532 --> 00:07:34.867
I'm not out of there yet.

00:07:35.911 --> 00:07:37.706
It's a place to hone my skills.

00:07:37.790 --> 00:07:39.669
For example,
I've been working to memorize

00:07:39.752 --> 00:07:42.215
all of our regulars'
coffee preferences.

00:07:42.298 --> 00:07:44.344
Which is no small task,
trust me.

00:07:44.427 --> 00:07:46.599
That sounds like
a seriously hard job!

00:07:46.683 --> 00:07:48.562
Wait, your coffee is so good

00:07:48.645 --> 00:07:50.732
because you're customizing
every cup?

00:07:50.816 --> 00:07:52.987
[KISAKI] Maa,
you like your coffee bitter

00:07:53.070 --> 00:07:54.281
and not too hot.

00:07:54.364 --> 00:07:57.245
Chi, you like plenty of cream,
but no sugar.

00:07:57.328 --> 00:07:59.499
The truth is,
I'm no coffee wizard.

00:07:59.584 --> 00:08:01.420
Might've been a cheap way
to impress you.

00:08:01.504 --> 00:08:04.009
But it did up your respect
for your manager.

00:08:04.092 --> 00:08:05.596
With all that said,

00:08:05.679 --> 00:08:07.683
you could both learn a lot
from barista training,

00:08:07.766 --> 00:08:09.520
and I still suggest you go.

00:08:10.271 --> 00:08:11.190
If you try your best

00:08:11.273 --> 00:08:13.528
to learn about the things
that seem small now,

00:08:13.612 --> 00:08:14.780
you'll be more prepared

00:08:14.864 --> 00:08:17.118
to learn about the things
that seem big later on.

00:08:18.370 --> 00:08:19.790
Any dream that's come true

00:08:19.874 --> 00:08:22.253
was achieved
through a series of small steps.

00:08:22.963 --> 00:08:24.007
We learn.

00:08:24.090 --> 00:08:26.554
And with some determination,
we grow.

00:08:26.638 --> 00:08:29.769
The greater your resolve,
the greater your dream can be.

00:08:29.852 --> 00:08:32.900
But, fear not.
I'm barely taking steps.

00:08:32.983 --> 00:08:37.367
Dreams take time to come true.
I apologize for the lecture.

00:08:37.450 --> 00:08:38.787
It's good to see you.

00:08:38.870 --> 00:08:39.914
Please come by MgR's

00:08:39.997 --> 00:08:41.668
next time
you're in the neighborhood.

00:08:41.751 --> 00:08:42.586
Good night.

00:08:43.462 --> 00:08:44.339
[gasps]

00:08:45.299 --> 00:08:46.134
[sighs]

00:08:47.011 --> 00:08:48.430
[KISAKI]
Oh, and chicken boy?

00:08:49.099 --> 00:08:50.184
I hear you're depressed

00:08:50.268 --> 00:08:52.021
because I banned you
from the store.

00:08:52.606 --> 00:08:53.525
[gasps]

00:08:53.608 --> 00:08:54.986
It's tricky.

00:08:55.069 --> 00:08:57.240
Part of me worries
I'm using your feelings for me

00:08:57.323 --> 00:08:58.325
to hurt your employer,

00:08:58.409 --> 00:09:00.956
even though that was never
my intention in the slightest.

00:09:01.039 --> 00:09:02.375
Disarming a business rival

00:09:02.458 --> 00:09:04.421
outside the realm of business
is wrong.

00:09:04.505 --> 00:09:06.759
A barman would never do
such a thing.

00:09:06.843 --> 00:09:08.638
Do you mean--

00:09:08.722 --> 00:09:10.601
Come by the shop
whenever you want.

00:09:11.101 --> 00:09:15.527
But step of out of line,
and I'll see your ass in court.

00:09:16.613 --> 00:09:17.531
[gasps]

00:09:17.614 --> 00:09:20.662
Awesome. So,
all's well that ends well, huh?

00:09:20.746 --> 00:09:22.165
Yeah. Wow.

00:09:22.875 --> 00:09:23.793
[sighs]

00:09:23.877 --> 00:09:25.421
Please try to control yourself!

00:09:25.505 --> 00:09:27.425
♪

00:09:27.509 --> 00:09:30.431
Mister Sariel, do you realize
that you're levitating?

00:09:30.515 --> 00:09:31.851
[INSTRUCTOR 215A]
We'll begin our course

00:09:31.934 --> 00:09:35.692
by watching this 20-minute video
showing you the MgCafé way.

00:09:35.776 --> 00:09:37.320
It's not
the most hands-on activity,

00:09:37.403 --> 00:09:39.950
but it should give you
a good idea of our mission here.

00:09:40.034 --> 00:09:43.374
Afterwards, we'll dive right
into the "meat" of this course.

00:09:43.457 --> 00:09:44.417
[instructor 215A chuckles]

00:09:45.837 --> 00:09:47.215
Please enjoy the video.

00:09:48.467 --> 00:09:53.352
♪

00:09:53.435 --> 00:09:55.649
[ERONE]
I'm confused. What's this?

00:09:56.818 --> 00:09:58.237
Farfarello isn't here.

00:09:58.822 --> 00:10:00.742
It's only you and me this time.

00:10:00.826 --> 00:10:02.788
You've been using
that big-ass barrier of yours

00:10:02.871 --> 00:10:04.207
to sneak around?

00:10:04.290 --> 00:10:06.461
It's my job to see
what you're up to.

00:10:06.546 --> 00:10:08.257
I'm supposed to find out
what you're doing here

00:10:08.340 --> 00:10:09.552
to achieve your mission.

00:10:10.094 --> 00:10:12.265
[ERONE]
So, what is this?

00:10:12.348 --> 00:10:14.520
Is it necessary
for world domination?

00:10:14.603 --> 00:10:16.106
Yup, that's why I'm here.

00:10:16.649 --> 00:10:17.985
I've got to take
every opportunity

00:10:18.068 --> 00:10:19.864
to study stuff like this.

00:10:19.947 --> 00:10:21.784
-"Study"?
-Yeah.

00:10:21.868 --> 00:10:23.495
You know, learning things.

00:10:23.580 --> 00:10:26.627
I'm taking some action to expand
my knowledge of this world.

00:10:26.711 --> 00:10:28.590
Oh. That makes sense.

00:10:29.340 --> 00:10:30.886
My army might've been strong,

00:10:30.969 --> 00:10:33.265
but they didn't have a clue
what it meant to be a nation.

00:10:33.933 --> 00:10:35.604
Or to fight for a cause.

00:10:36.021 --> 00:10:38.192
That's why I'm here in Japan.
This place?

00:10:38.275 --> 00:10:41.114
It's the perfect playground
to figure that stuff out.

00:10:41.198 --> 00:10:42.576
This class is a part of it.

00:10:43.202 --> 00:10:45.122
I'm taking small steps for now.

00:10:45.832 --> 00:10:48.045
I've got a new dream
for world conquest.

00:10:48.128 --> 00:10:49.673
It'll just take some time.

00:10:49.757 --> 00:10:52.303
A new dream. I see.

00:10:52.888 --> 00:10:53.973
Sounds like fun.

00:10:54.767 --> 00:10:55.936
[gasps]

00:10:56.019 --> 00:10:57.480
[gasps]

00:10:57.564 --> 00:10:59.777
[INSTRUCTOR 215A]
On to today's lecture.

00:10:59.860 --> 00:11:02.031
Everyone,
please open your texts.

00:11:05.705 --> 00:11:07.584
Hey, Chi. Back there--

00:11:07.668 --> 00:11:08.670
[gasps]

00:11:10.089 --> 00:11:11.049
Huh?

00:11:13.596 --> 00:11:15.182
Come with me. Please.

00:11:15.266 --> 00:11:16.268
[gasps]

00:11:18.230 --> 00:11:19.942
Mm. All right.

00:11:23.031 --> 00:11:26.622
[indistinct chatter]

00:11:26.706 --> 00:11:28.417
-[Maou gasps]
-[EMI] Hm?

00:11:28.500 --> 00:11:30.421
Uh, why's he here?

00:11:30.505 --> 00:11:31.674
He seems erratic.

00:11:32.341 --> 00:11:33.928
Where is the good Chiho?

00:11:34.012 --> 00:11:35.431
-[panting]
-[EMI] Maou!

00:11:36.349 --> 00:11:37.351
Have you seen Chi?

00:11:37.435 --> 00:11:39.230
She's supposed to be
at the class with you.

00:11:39.314 --> 00:11:40.650
When did you lose her?

00:11:40.734 --> 00:11:41.819
A few minutes ago.

00:11:42.738 --> 00:11:45.451
Nobody just vanishes
out of thin air like that.

00:11:45.535 --> 00:11:48.958
I'm almost 100% certain
Erone's barrier was involved.

00:11:49.042 --> 00:11:52.423
If you're going to beg,
I suppose I can help you.

00:11:52.507 --> 00:11:53.801
[all gasp]

00:11:53.885 --> 00:11:55.930
That ring she wears
on her left hand,

00:11:56.014 --> 00:11:58.435
it contains a shard of Yessod,
yes?

00:11:58.519 --> 00:11:59.647
Moon Mirror!

00:12:00.523 --> 00:12:05.366
[sparkling]

00:12:05.449 --> 00:12:06.869
[all gasp]

00:12:06.953 --> 00:12:07.954
How anticlimactic.

00:12:08.038 --> 00:12:09.583
She's a stone's throw away.

00:12:09.667 --> 00:12:10.627
Really, where?

00:12:10.710 --> 00:12:12.213
As fate would have it,

00:12:12.296 --> 00:12:14.969
there's a barrier pitched right
on the roof of that building.

00:12:15.970 --> 00:12:19.394
[wind rushing]

00:12:19.978 --> 00:12:21.398
[MAOU]
Real sorry, ladies.

00:12:21.481 --> 00:12:23.653
But I'm going to need
to borrow your power.

00:12:23.736 --> 00:12:26.032
And how do you expect us
to give it to you?

00:12:26.826 --> 00:12:28.538
[MAOU]
I noticed something.

00:12:28.621 --> 00:12:30.165
I'm like Chi.

00:12:30.249 --> 00:12:32.378
I'm a human being now,
the same as her.

00:12:32.461 --> 00:12:33.338
Huh?

00:12:33.965 --> 00:12:36.887
I understand
you came here willingly.

00:12:36.971 --> 00:12:38.808
Why didn't you try to resist?

00:12:38.891 --> 00:12:40.645
I was pretty sure
that you would beat me up

00:12:40.729 --> 00:12:42.273
if I tried to fight back.

00:12:42.774 --> 00:12:44.026
Interesting.

00:12:44.110 --> 00:12:46.699
You have steadier nerves
than your appearance suggests.

00:12:46.782 --> 00:12:47.909
Gee, thanks!

00:12:47.993 --> 00:12:49.705
I've been through
some scary stuff.

00:12:49.788 --> 00:12:51.959
[FARFARELLO]
Have you? Well...

00:12:53.295 --> 00:12:54.757
[smoke rushing]

00:12:54.840 --> 00:12:55.967
[gasps]

00:12:58.388 --> 00:12:59.975
How does this compare?

00:13:00.935 --> 00:13:03.733
Oh. You were wearing undies
under there?

00:13:03.816 --> 00:13:05.360
Behold my true form.

00:13:05.444 --> 00:13:07.073
Cower in fear, girl.

00:13:07.156 --> 00:13:09.912
Uh, you know, I was kind of
expecting something

00:13:09.995 --> 00:13:11.372
a little bit more dramatic.

00:13:12.374 --> 00:13:13.210
Hush, child,

00:13:13.293 --> 00:13:15.840
you're merely feeding my desire
to skin you alive.

00:13:15.924 --> 00:13:18.220
Oops. Sorry, Mister. Uh...

00:13:18.971 --> 00:13:20.892
Just so you know,
Satan hasn't come close

00:13:20.975 --> 00:13:23.146
to giving up on his dream
of ruling the world.

00:13:23.940 --> 00:13:25.568
He's learning a whole lot.

00:13:26.027 --> 00:13:28.616
Like new strategies
to strengthen his campaign.

00:13:28.699 --> 00:13:30.118
He's studying.

00:13:30.202 --> 00:13:31.831
Yup! Studying hard.

00:13:32.373 --> 00:13:34.252
Mister? Real quick question.

00:13:34.795 --> 00:13:38.134
Satan.
Why'd he ever invade Ente Isla?

00:13:38.928 --> 00:13:40.055
What does that place have

00:13:40.138 --> 00:13:42.309
that made you guys want
to conquer it so bad?

00:13:42.978 --> 00:13:43.896
Funny.

00:13:43.980 --> 00:13:45.399
Why do you care to know?

00:13:45.482 --> 00:13:46.902
To help him.

00:13:47.486 --> 00:13:48.656
If I can figure out

00:13:48.739 --> 00:13:50.535
why it went wrong
the first time,

00:13:50.618 --> 00:13:53.206
I can help make
his dream come true now!

00:13:53.290 --> 00:13:55.670
[CHIHO] He's seemed
really confused lately.

00:13:55.753 --> 00:13:57.883
He keeps saying
the way he did things last time

00:13:57.966 --> 00:13:58.968
was wrong.

00:13:59.051 --> 00:13:59.970
Damn, girl.

00:14:00.053 --> 00:14:02.433
A multi-recipient idea link
so soon?

00:14:02.517 --> 00:14:04.688
She shouldn't be capable
of such a feat yet.

00:14:04.771 --> 00:14:08.320
Do you think that she's somehow
doing it subconsciously?

00:14:10.909 --> 00:14:13.246
Why? You're an average human,
aren't you?

00:14:13.330 --> 00:14:14.875
100%, Sir.

00:14:14.958 --> 00:14:16.210
Then explain.

00:14:16.294 --> 00:14:19.300
Why would you choose to help
us demons over your own kind?

00:14:19.383 --> 00:14:21.931
Hush. No demons versus humans!

00:14:22.014 --> 00:14:23.601
They can get along.

00:14:23.684 --> 00:14:26.607
If they can do it now,
they can do it forever!

00:14:26.690 --> 00:14:28.151
There's some way
to rule the world

00:14:28.234 --> 00:14:30.657
where the Devil
and the Hero can be friends!

00:14:30.740 --> 00:14:31.825
[both panting]

00:14:32.159 --> 00:14:35.123
This dream, it might not look
like same kind of world

00:14:35.207 --> 00:14:36.417
conquest he tried before,

00:14:36.502 --> 00:14:38.923
but it's worth a real shot
if you ask me.

00:14:39.006 --> 00:14:40.425
[FARFARELLO]
What does it look like?

00:14:40.510 --> 00:14:42.221
Devil and Hero unite.

00:14:42.304 --> 00:14:43.516
Everyone is happy!

00:14:44.225 --> 00:14:45.979
And demons and humans
work together,

00:14:46.062 --> 00:14:47.732
so they all get enough to eat.

00:14:48.441 --> 00:14:50.237
That's what I want to see.

00:14:50.320 --> 00:14:52.199
That's what I'm going to help
make happen!

00:14:54.788 --> 00:14:57.209
Look, Farfarello. A barrier.

00:14:57.292 --> 00:14:58.587
[gasps]

00:14:59.798 --> 00:15:02.971
♪

00:15:03.681 --> 00:15:04.975
[CHIHO]
Mister Maou?

00:15:05.058 --> 00:15:06.269
You good, Chi?

00:15:06.352 --> 00:15:07.814
[CHIHO]
Yup! All safe!

00:15:08.816 --> 00:15:10.737
[sparkling]

00:15:10.820 --> 00:15:12.489
Wait! No fighting!

00:15:12.574 --> 00:15:15.245
Mister Farfa-Fellow
hasn't been mean to me at all!

00:15:15.328 --> 00:15:17.249
Farfarello.

00:15:17.332 --> 00:15:18.586
Chi might be a sweetie,

00:15:18.669 --> 00:15:20.923
but it's obvious
you kidnapped my friend.

00:15:21.007 --> 00:15:22.969
Sorry, but I'm not feeling
quite as sweet.

00:15:23.470 --> 00:15:24.765
What's your game, panties?

00:15:24.848 --> 00:15:25.933
All due respect.

00:15:26.017 --> 00:15:27.102
I wanted to be thorough

00:15:27.186 --> 00:15:30.025
and hear your story
from a third party, my lord.

00:15:30.108 --> 00:15:31.486
I had questions, too.

00:15:31.570 --> 00:15:33.323
About what Ente Isla's like.

00:15:33.406 --> 00:15:36.120
And why you and your army wanted
to conquer it so much.

00:15:36.204 --> 00:15:37.791
[sighs] I see.

00:15:38.374 --> 00:15:40.003
Next time, guys.

00:15:40.087 --> 00:15:41.924
Just ask me that crap
to my face.

00:15:42.007 --> 00:15:42.926
[both gasps]

00:15:43.009 --> 00:15:46.558
I'm always here.
And questions don't scare me.

00:15:46.642 --> 00:15:48.478
Right! I'm sorry!

00:15:48.562 --> 00:15:50.315
-[MAOU] Farfarello.
-Sire?

00:15:50.398 --> 00:15:52.654
Ever seen something
like this before?

00:15:52.737 --> 00:15:54.240
[FARFARELLO]
I have, my lord.

00:15:54.323 --> 00:15:57.454
It's what humans trade
for goods and services.

00:15:57.539 --> 00:15:59.250
Right. It's called money.

00:15:59.333 --> 00:16:00.586
Forget about magic,

00:16:00.670 --> 00:16:03.592
this bill is tons more powerful
than that junk.

00:16:03.676 --> 00:16:05.972
[FARFARELLO] You claim
that a measly scrap of paper

00:16:06.055 --> 00:16:08.309
has more power
than magic itself?

00:16:08.393 --> 00:16:10.188
[MAOU]
We give it power.

00:16:10.272 --> 00:16:13.361
What we decide
shapes the world around us.

00:16:13.444 --> 00:16:15.282
That's just one of the things
I've picked up on

00:16:15.365 --> 00:16:16.618
during my time here.

00:16:16.702 --> 00:16:18.079
[FARFARELLO]
Still, my lord.

00:16:18.163 --> 00:16:21.587
What could something so small
mean in the face of true might?

00:16:21.670 --> 00:16:22.922
Nothing yet.

00:16:23.006 --> 00:16:27.097
But, in time, if I build
this system the right way,

00:16:27.181 --> 00:16:28.893
even the Hero,

00:16:28.976 --> 00:16:31.355
the one whose mission
it was to kill me,

00:16:31.439 --> 00:16:34.111
will give me power
for cold hard cash.

00:16:35.948 --> 00:16:37.034
Next time,

00:16:37.117 --> 00:16:38.787
let's figure out a way
to express that

00:16:38.871 --> 00:16:41.334
that doesn't make me sound
like a sword-slinging pimp.

00:16:41.417 --> 00:16:42.962
Hey, Chi. Show time.

00:16:43.046 --> 00:16:45.258
-[gasps]
-I've got some work to do.

00:16:45.342 --> 00:16:47.262
-Keep yourself safe.
-[CHIHO] Huh?

00:16:52.690 --> 00:16:55.111
Sire, please tell me
the meaning of this at once!

00:16:55.195 --> 00:16:56.280
Stay there!

00:16:56.907 --> 00:16:59.078
You better be able to handle
this much force!

00:16:59.161 --> 00:17:01.290
There's no reason to worry,
ladies.

00:17:01.374 --> 00:17:04.004
Just watch.
I'll blow your minds.

00:17:04.088 --> 00:17:06.342
-[yells]
-Be careful!

00:17:10.392 --> 00:17:13.983
[CHIHO] ♪ <i>The sun is up
It's morning once again ♪</i>

00:17:14.066 --> 00:17:17.865
<i>♪ The day is full of hope, so ♪</i>

00:17:17.949 --> 00:17:21.581
<i>♪ Look up to the sky
And reach up to the clouds ♪</i>

00:17:21.665 --> 00:17:25.213
<i>♪ As the radio guides you ♪</i>

00:17:25.297 --> 00:17:28.762
<i>♪ So, breathe deeply
And think sweet thoughts ♪</i>

00:17:28.846 --> 00:17:32.227
<i>♪ And take in
The beauty of the world ♪</i>

00:17:32.311 --> 00:17:35.693
<i>♪ And feel joyful and hopeful
And grateful today ♪</i>

00:17:35.776 --> 00:17:38.866
Starting. Three. Two. One!

00:17:39.618 --> 00:17:40.786
Jeez, that hurt.

00:17:40.870 --> 00:17:42.874
Thought I might pass out
for a second there.

00:17:42.957 --> 00:17:44.753
He's so huge.

00:17:44.836 --> 00:17:46.757
This is quite unheard of.

00:17:46.840 --> 00:17:48.677
What the heck
just happened to you?

00:17:48.761 --> 00:17:50.556
You know the answer,
don't you, Chi?

00:17:50.639 --> 00:17:52.184
Uh, I think so.

00:17:53.227 --> 00:17:56.150
When a body gets
an overdose of celestial force,

00:17:56.233 --> 00:17:58.154
it starts producing magic.

00:17:58.237 --> 00:18:01.077
Most cases result
in a nasty poisoning.

00:18:01.160 --> 00:18:02.037
But I had a feeling

00:18:02.120 --> 00:18:04.542
that Sadou Maou's body
wouldn't be so easy to break,

00:18:04.626 --> 00:18:06.170
and I was right.

00:18:06.253 --> 00:18:08.049
Next time,
just give us a heads up

00:18:08.132 --> 00:18:10.679
when we're participants
in some whack job experiment!

00:18:10.763 --> 00:18:12.683
King Satan, I--

00:18:12.767 --> 00:18:15.815
You what? Are you satisfied now?

00:18:17.192 --> 00:18:20.365
I was very rash and thoughtless
in my actions, my lord.

00:18:20.448 --> 00:18:21.492
I'm sorry.

00:18:21.576 --> 00:18:24.206
Punish me for my crime
however you see fit.

00:18:24.289 --> 00:18:26.711
Skip punishment
and do me a favor.

00:18:27.462 --> 00:18:29.843
When you get home,
go tell Barbariccia.

00:18:30.719 --> 00:18:32.264
There's a new army.

00:18:32.347 --> 00:18:35.813
And it's led by me
and the Four Great Generals 2.0.

00:18:35.896 --> 00:18:37.357
Allow me to introduce them.

00:18:37.441 --> 00:18:38.861
[ALL]
Huh?

00:18:38.944 --> 00:18:42.409
Hm. Firstly, Alciel and Lucifer.

00:18:42.492 --> 00:18:43.537
You remember them.

00:18:43.620 --> 00:18:45.248
As for new additions...

00:18:45.331 --> 00:18:46.960
The Hero Emilia.

00:18:47.043 --> 00:18:48.505
She's an expert
on the battlefield,

00:18:48.589 --> 00:18:50.718
and might be even stronger
than me.

00:18:50.801 --> 00:18:51.720
"Might"?

00:18:51.803 --> 00:18:54.224
[MAOU] Doctrinal Correction
Council Investigator,

00:18:54.308 --> 00:18:55.477
Death Scythe Bel.

00:18:55.561 --> 00:18:56.437
With her background

00:18:56.521 --> 00:18:58.274
in the Church's
Missionary Division,

00:18:58.357 --> 00:19:01.447
her wisdom on Ente Isla affairs
makes her invaluable.

00:19:01.531 --> 00:19:02.742
Huh? It does?

00:19:02.825 --> 00:19:05.706
[MAOU] Finally, the woman
who turns enemies into allies.

00:19:05.790 --> 00:19:08.837
The crux of our operation
to win hearts and my aide,

00:19:08.921 --> 00:19:11.676
future MgRonald's barista
Chiho Sasaki!

00:19:11.760 --> 00:19:12.929
[gasps]

00:19:13.012 --> 00:19:14.849
All of them will serve

00:19:14.933 --> 00:19:17.730
as the four great generals
of the new Devil's army.

00:19:17.814 --> 00:19:18.815
[SUZUNO, EMI]
That's five!

00:19:18.899 --> 00:19:19.901
And what the hell?

00:19:19.984 --> 00:19:21.613
You've got to have
a conversation with someone

00:19:21.696 --> 00:19:24.284
before you declare them
your general all willy-nilly!

00:19:24.368 --> 00:19:27.290
No way, I'm a general now?

00:19:27.374 --> 00:19:29.754
Please!
That is no reason to smile!

00:19:29.838 --> 00:19:32.133
Seems they're having
a grand time.

00:19:32.217 --> 00:19:34.514
This no longer
warrants a barrier.

00:19:36.601 --> 00:19:37.520
Huh?

00:19:37.603 --> 00:19:40.441
Here, take it.
King Satan's magic.

00:19:40.526 --> 00:19:42.445
Thank you, my lord.

00:19:42.530 --> 00:19:45.703
This is all great news,
and will surely boost morale.

00:19:45.786 --> 00:19:47.874
Leave my name
out of your "news", got it?

00:19:47.957 --> 00:19:50.086
[sparkling]

00:19:50.754 --> 00:19:52.800
-Ah.
-Erone!

00:19:52.883 --> 00:19:55.806
Hi, Alas Ramus. Long time.

00:19:55.890 --> 00:19:56.891
[giggles]

00:19:56.975 --> 00:19:58.729
The others. They good?

00:19:58.812 --> 00:20:00.858
Don't know. I wish I did.

00:20:00.941 --> 00:20:02.945
Sorry. But I'm good.

00:20:03.947 --> 00:20:05.618
Let's play real soon!

00:20:05.701 --> 00:20:06.661
Let's.

00:20:06.745 --> 00:20:09.959
♪

00:20:14.552 --> 00:20:16.430
You must correct the record.

00:20:16.514 --> 00:20:18.392
There can't be
five "four generals."

00:20:18.476 --> 00:20:19.854
Who says there can't be?

00:20:19.938 --> 00:20:21.650
That sounds just peachy to me.

00:20:21.733 --> 00:20:23.277
Hell, I'd take six.

00:20:23.361 --> 00:20:24.572
If you already want more,

00:20:24.656 --> 00:20:26.492
then replacing me
should be no issue.

00:20:26.576 --> 00:20:28.872
Papa! Pick me!

00:20:28.955 --> 00:20:30.751
You're the Colonel of Cuteness!

00:20:30.834 --> 00:20:32.212
Haven't you
arbitrarily thrown out

00:20:32.295 --> 00:20:34.299
enough nonsense titles today?

00:20:34.383 --> 00:20:36.303
[sighs] Whatever, then.

00:20:36.387 --> 00:20:39.267
If you think your general-ship
is really such nonsense,

00:20:39.351 --> 00:20:41.230
well,
let's say you're tagging along

00:20:41.313 --> 00:20:42.692
to keep eyes on me.

00:20:43.484 --> 00:20:44.696
-What?
-Huh?

00:20:44.779 --> 00:20:47.242
Come on. I know
that you're in a weird spot.

00:20:47.785 --> 00:20:49.329
You don't know
whether to keep treating me

00:20:49.413 --> 00:20:51.083
as an enemy or as a friend.

00:20:51.751 --> 00:20:53.630
So maybe we can start fresh.

00:20:53.714 --> 00:20:55.926
Decide for yourself
if I'm your enemy.

00:20:56.845 --> 00:20:59.224
-Sound good?
-Yeah, on opposite day.

00:20:59.809 --> 00:21:01.228
Just give me a chance.

00:21:01.311 --> 00:21:03.357
If you're willing to start
our relationship over,

00:21:03.441 --> 00:21:04.317
clean slate,

00:21:04.401 --> 00:21:06.990
I swear I'll show you
I'm not the Devil you think.

00:21:07.073 --> 00:21:09.829
Emi the Hero. Let's be a team.

00:21:10.664 --> 00:21:12.333
As I build a new world,

00:21:12.417 --> 00:21:15.006
I'll show you how incredible
that world can be.

00:21:15.089 --> 00:21:16.008
[gasps]

00:21:17.093 --> 00:21:18.137
[gasps]

00:21:18.220 --> 00:21:20.851
Wow. Game recognizes game.

00:21:20.934 --> 00:21:22.563
You're such a stupid jerk!

00:21:22.646 --> 00:21:24.734
Do you have a clue what any
of that mushy crap implies,

00:21:24.817 --> 00:21:27.030
you oblivious dumpster fire
of a demon?

00:21:27.113 --> 00:21:28.992
Huh? [grunts]

00:21:29.075 --> 00:21:30.286
Uh, 'sup, Chi?

00:21:30.369 --> 00:21:31.790
Nothing much.

00:21:32.415 --> 00:21:34.169
Let's go and buy me some cake.

00:21:34.252 --> 00:21:35.379
Huh?

00:21:35.463 --> 00:21:38.219
My birthday is coming up,
so you owe me cake, silly.

00:21:38.302 --> 00:21:40.389
But why right now?
Don't get me wrong.

00:21:40.473 --> 00:21:42.770
I was planning to get you
a present and stuff.

00:21:42.853 --> 00:21:44.524
Uh, for some weird reason,

00:21:44.607 --> 00:21:46.778
I get the feeling
you're mad at me, too.

00:21:46.861 --> 00:21:48.949
Am I? Whelp, time to go!

00:21:49.742 --> 00:21:51.453
-Jeez, Chi!
-Cakey! Cakey!

00:21:51.538 --> 00:21:54.544
Friends make us fresh
and put courage in our breasts.

00:21:54.627 --> 00:21:57.131
And now off to dinner
this angel must go!

00:21:57.215 --> 00:21:59.302
Time for my first MgCafé!

00:23:29.900 --> 00:23:32.071
[indistinct chatter]

00:23:32.155 --> 00:23:33.490
-[SUZUNO] Emilia.
-Hm?

00:23:34.117 --> 00:23:36.371
There is something
rather pressing

00:23:36.455 --> 00:23:37.666
that we need to discuss.

00:23:38.292 --> 00:23:41.173
We learned
that angels are people. Yes?

00:23:41.549 --> 00:23:45.264
If that much is true,
what does that make demons?

